{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"compacted_at":1784653321542611002,"compiled_state":{"alias":"autumnal-defectible-xeme","assignee":"","author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","authorship":{"signed":5,"unsigned":0},"authorship_ledger":[{"content_hash":"ee0dc9ef991f58b533604ffedefa86386985c8663f4e3e891e093a4767236591","event_uuid":"863f30fa-60d4-4a48-a20b-02f08c4298c4","position":{"commit_sha":"39175f4505b500aed16f86030b5d477ad4003a1d","position":"1784517024902453001-863f30fa-60d4-4a48-a20b-02f08c4298c4"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"5a7e413aff7d49a0563453bfd3cb783bbedf693950f85afa1015073467b1db25","event_uuid":"339b446c-0bbb-478d-a804-7da8b1e2418f","position":{"commit_sha":"61787f794673d2e087121dacd212a31c50d4371f","position":"1784652885944384001-339b446c-0bbb-478d-a804-7da8b1e2418f"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"d074dee3e3e5c3674bbb1f7e9d93a64fc6497354885db55368ad7d54a8b61080","event_uuid":"c5fe2e4f-a384-4805-887a-2dbcebf7683a","position":{"commit_sha":"61787f794673d2e087121dacd212a31c50d4371f","position":"1784652886248655001-c5fe2e4f-a384-4805-887a-2dbcebf7683a"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"cfb844837fe5b8b8ed00ccb020fa976b076067e17b6d54bb5e741f26a73c4b69","event_uuid":"11b9cf31-723d-49ec-bce2-3ab9601af07e","position":{"commit_sha":"433995507915c56475b6c3acf0083f8d0e3898bf","position":"1784653112463992306-11b9cf31-723d-49ec-bce2-3ab9601af07e"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"3a2a7461349460455f64a75ce7f205dfd25f67699267ec95e0359b44f1a423c1","event_uuid":"bda86e34-3f4d-40ac-a4b4-f2d81ad610be","position":{"commit_sha":"6176bc7b0252f3477ca40aec8bca3c1d3769fcc3","position":"1784653321542611001-bda86e34-3f4d-40ac-a4b4-f2d81ad610be"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":null,"claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":null,"comments":[{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"REBAR-DEBUG DIAGNOSIS (2026-07-21)\n\nReproduced on current origin/main with rebar metrics --output json: attempts_per_ticket, rework_within_7_days, revert_recovery, reopen_recovery, first_pass_rate, cost_per_accepted_change, env_diagnosis_intervals, and first_pass_verification all render unavailable with reason \"Invalid isoformat string: ''\".\n\nRoot cause: src/rebar/_commands/metrics.py normalizes absent or empty --since/--until to empty strings, places them in the context, and fault-isolates each resulting reader exception. src/rebar/metrics/event_metrics.py _bounds treats every non-None value as parseable and calls datetime.fromisoformat(\"\"). Git readers independently tolerate empty values, producing the inconsistent partial report. Fault isolation masks the boundary contract violation as metric unavailability.\n\nMinimal corrective seam: normalize the default window once in metrics_cli to concrete ISO dates for today and today-30d, make explicit blank values follow the same rule, keep reader functions defensive, update help/docs, and add a no-flags interface regression that asserts real ticket-derived values and the reported output bounds.\n\nNo code changed during this diagnostic run.","timestamp":1784653321542611001}],"created_at":1784517024902453001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[],"description":"## Problem\nRunning `rebar metrics` with NO `--since/--until` (the default invocation) silently breaks every ticket-derived (agent_process) metric. The CLI defaults the flags to empty strings and passes them into the readers; `metrics.event_metrics._bounds(\"\")` calls `datetime.fromisoformat(\"\")` which raises `ValueError: Invalid isoformat string: ''`. The CLI's per-metric fault isolation catches it and renders each metric as `unavailable` with reason=\"Invalid isoformat string: ''\", so the failure is silent.\n\n## Reproduced (in the rebar repo itself)\n`rebar metrics --output json` -> attempts_per_ticket / first_pass_rate / revert_recovery / reopen_recovery / rework_within_7_days all report `{unavailable: {reason: \"Invalid isoformat string: ''\"}}`.\nWith explicit dates (`--since 2026-01-01 --until 2026-12-31`) they compute correctly (e.g. first_pass_rate -> 0.9984). The git readers guard the empty string (churn returns data); the event/sidecar readers do not — an inconsistency.\n\n## Expected\nWith no `--since/--until`, default the window to the **last 30 days** (until=today, since=today-30d) rather than passing empty strings. Empty/whitespace date values should normalize to this default (or to `None` open bounds) at the CLI boundary so no reader ever receives an unparseable string.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] `rebar metrics` with no date flags returns real values for the agent_process metrics over a last-30-days window (no 'Invalid isoformat' unavailable).\n- [ ] Default window documented in `rebar metrics --help`, user-guide, and the help text file.\n- [ ] Explicit `--since/--until` still override the default; explicit empty-string values are handled gracefully.\n- [ ] Unit/interface test covering the no-flags invocation (regression: currently masked as unavailable).","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[],"parent_id":null,"parent_status_uuid":"339b446c-0bbb-478d-a804-7da8b1e2418f","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["metrics","cli"],"ticket_id":"a060-e873-2e0c-4721","ticket_type":"bug","title":"rebar metrics with no --since/--until fails ticket-derived metrics; default to last 30 days","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["863f30fa-60d4-4a48-a20b-02f08c4298c4","339b446c-0bbb-478d-a804-7da8b1e2418f","c5fe2e4f-a384-4805-887a-2dbcebf7683a","11b9cf31-723d-49ec-bce2-3ab9601af07e","bda86e34-3f4d-40ac-a4b4-f2d81ad610be"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784653321542611002,"uuid":"45d6e828-2cdc-4eb0-ba98-29ee6c70e6cb"}